<img src="http://altonsunphoto.smugmug.com/photos/i-F4FZLZ2/0/M/i-F4FZLZ2-M.jpg" alt="Moments from Meteor Devshop 2" width=560> **Meteor Devshop 2.**  Meteorites being excellent to each other: drop in, plug in, and help each other build things. ([Meteor Devshop Photo Album](https://plus.google.com/photos/104063475472216743156/albums/5864967841567586593))

Last month's [Meteor Devshop](http://www.meetup.com/Meteor-SFBay/events/106842372/), our [monthly](http://www.meteor.com/blog/2013/02/06/meteor-devshop-0-share-knowledge-not-germs) [co-working](http://www.meteor.com/blog/2013/03/08/meteor-devshop-1-the-shape-of-things-to-come) [meetup](https://meetup.com/Meteor-SFBay/), was the largest ever with over 110 Meteorites in attendance. A lot of Meteorites who dropped in for [Meteor Devshop 1](../blog/2013/03/08/meteor-devshop-1-the-shape-of-things-to-come) have made some amazing progress, which was great to see.  Also at this Devshop, other Meteorites announced that they are seeking to [hire Meteorites](mailto:community@meteor.com) to make apps.  

<img src="http://i1304.photobucket.com/albums/s534/yalicemeteor/wide_crowd_zps183aa064.jpg" alt="Panorama from Meteor Devshop 2">**Meteor Devshop 2.**  More Meteorites in one place. ([Meteor Devshop Photo Album](https://plus.google.com/photos/104063475472216743156/albums/5864967841567586593))

## Tech Talks at Meteor Devshop

There have been [some truly amazing talks at Meteor Devshop](http://www.26plays.com/playlist/g7x4jagy6sxyJWdYt) lately, which leads to the need to keep track of them efficiently. The solution, [26Plays](http://www.26plays.com), is playlist management made beautiful.  It is a Meteor app that makes it possible to collaboratively construct and share playlists across video providers.  And for the foreseeable future, [26Plays](http://www.26plays.com) will be my personal go-to method for organizing tech talk videos. Thank you so much, [Benjamin Chelli](https://github.com/benjaminchelli), for building this.

### Lightning Talks

The [Lightning Talks for Meteor Devshop 2](http://www.26plays.com/playlist/wAS7Ld6oReWXLkPdz) showcased the amazing work of Meteorites from this past month. 

- [Howard Tang](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vkEHaK6RxN8) showed off [Routrrr](http://routrrr.meteor.com), which is a shared Google map that makes it easier for friends to meet up at cafes located between them.  

- [Ben Morrow](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yf1kDRW8BL4) demo'd Draggables, a simple cross-platform proof-of-concept game.  

- As [seen on Hacker News](https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=5387847), [Mike Adams](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0ES28pZ4AZE)'s [Instahood](http://instahood.meteor.com) is the Instagraph/GoogleMaps integration that allows you to see Instagram pictures from anywhere in the world.  

- [David Glasser](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mXJgOwn5FbY) previewed the new features of [Meteor 0.6.0](https://github.com/meteor/meteor/blob/devel/History.md#v060): the new release system, NPM integration, and app packages. 

- [Dror Matalon](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dToSn_FOISI) shared [Meteor SQL](https://github.com/drorm/meteor-sql), that is, how to use mySQL with Meteor, and how it works.  

- [John Katsnelson](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4a50-5NluMk) showcased [Deface](http://deface.meteor.com), a way to deface pictures in true MS Paint style.  

- [Gavin McDermott](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ViOslmSDogI) shared his [Rooms smart package](https://github.com/gavinmcdermott/rooms), and walks through how to use it to easily define chat rooms.  

- Last but not least, [James Gill and Mike Risse](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GA0s-TM3Kzg) showed off [MadEye.io](http://madeye.io) and what they can do in 3 minutes of impressively intense collaborative live-coding in the browser.   

']],'

