**Meteor Devshop 4.** Meteorites working, mingling, and helping each other. ([Meteor Devshop 4 Photo Album](https://plus.google.com/photos/104063475472216743156/albums/5886914072358965873))

Last month's Devshop focused on what goes into developing more complex Meteor applications, featuring talks on [test driven development](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ac9ou9Vi0q8), [performance optimization](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xoBCtXbjeJw), and other [subjects of keen interest](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DK00w1f4-f4). It was inspiring to watch startups and consulting shops share their projects, best practices, and app betas. Devshop 4 was also our first event to feature live-streaming (via the [Meteor YouTube channel](http://videos.meteor.com)), making it possible for Meteorites around the world to pull up a chair. Special thanks to all you YouTube subscribers and to Meteorites [Troy Clark](https://twitter.com/RaptBlue) and [Jack Saunders](https://twitter.com/ExoniaNetwork.com) of the [Exonia Network](http://www.exonianetwork.com). 

##Test Driven Development using Meteor

Many of you had already heard of [Sam Hatoum](http://xolv.io/)'s TDD work through [Twitter](https://twitter.com/meteorjs/status/324904436088598528), [Meteor-talk](https://groups.google.com/d/topic/meteor-talk/3QEhNXq2Rb4/discussion), and [other community channels](http://meteor.com/blog/2013/04/25/this-week-in-meteor). His blog posts and github project page have been shared widely, and it was wonderful hearing him speak in person on this subject. Sam is a self-described "testing geek" and the founder of [xolv.io](http://xolv.io/), a product delivery consulting firm. During his talk, he shared xolv.io's approach to [unit testing](http://blog.xolv.io/2013/04/unit-testing-with-meteor.html), [end-to-end testing](http://blog.xolv.io/2013/04/end-to-end-testing-for-web-apps-meteor.html), and acceptance testing in Meteor. He also explained his ["Real-Time Development" (RTD)](http://xolvio.github.io/rtd/) project, a test runner for Meteor that emphasizes ultra-quick feedback.

']],'

