**Meteor Devshop 5.** Learning from each other. ([Meteor Devshop 5 Photo Album](https://plus.google.com/photos/104063475472216743156/albums/5901347232565821457))

Devshop 5 featured tech talks by three Meteorites who are each in an exciting stage of their Meteor projects. [Adrian Lanning](https://github.com/alanning) is CTO of [ShareWith911](http://www.sharewith911.com/), which launched six months ago and recently passed 100K in revenue, having been adopted by 30+ school districts. [Casey Cobb](http://caseycobb.com/) is a partner at [Project Ricochet](http://projectricochet.com/), which just launched the public beta of [PushPinPlanner](http://pushpinplanner.com/), a collaborative resource planning app. Finally, [Chris Mather](https://twitter.com/cdmather) is gearing up for a major redesign of [EventedMind](http://www.eventedmind.com/), which hosts his popular Meteor screencasts. They used the Devshop stage to dive into the technology underpinning their projects and share what they know with the rest of the Meteor community. 

With growing interest in the Devshop talks, we wanted to find a way to bring them to the worldwide Meteor community, right as they happen.  We're delighted to announce that we will be broadcasting each month's tech talks and lightning talks at [devshoplive.meteor.com](http://devshoplive.meteor.com), which will direct you to the next scheduled event or to the [Meteor YouTube channel](http://videos.meteor.com). Talks will begin at 7pm PST, typically on the last Thursday of each month, and will also viewable afterwards as a recording. I hope many of you will join us this [Thursday, July 25th](http://devshop6.meteor.com/). In addition to audience questions, the speakers will take a few live questions from viewers: just tweet in with [#MeteorDevshop](https://twitter.com/search?q=%23meteordevshop&src=typd).

##Authorization, Performance, and Routing

[Adrian Lanning](https://github.com/alanning) spoke about authorization using the [meteor-roles package](https://github.com/alanning/meteor-roles), which he authored for use in his production application, [ShareWith911](http://www.sharewith911.com/). He covered access control basics and illustrated how authorization is used in [ShareWith911](http://www.sharewith911.com/). The app helps teachers, administrators, and first responders communicate during school emergencies, and meteor-roles allows different users to be authorized for different sets of actions. He demonstrated basic usage of the package, discussed best practices, and shared several further resources including [source code](https://github.com/alanning/meteor-roles), an [example page](http://roles.meteor.com/), and [documentation](http://alanning.github.com/meteor-roles). 

Adrian's cofounder and CEO is [Erik Endress](https://twitter.com/erikendress), a former first responder, school board member, and recipient of the NYC Award for Heroism. Adrian and Erik are looking for remote, freelance Meteor developers. You can contact them using the [ShareWith911 contact page](http://www.sharewith911.com/contact).

']],'

