[Casey Cobb](http://caseycobb.com/) prefaced his talk with a call to action for Meteor early adopters, urging Meteorites to contribute knowledge back through [Stack Overflow](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/meteor), [blog posts](http://projectricochet.com/blog), and other [community hubs](https://groups.google.com/forum/?fromgroups#!forum/meteor-talk). Casey's open source consulting shop â [Project Ricochet](http://projectricochet.com/) â walks the talk by publishing their own Meteor lessons on their blog. Devshop 4 included a lightning talk about one popular post - â[Improving the Performance of your Meteor JS projects](http://projectricochet.com/blog/meteor-js-performance#.Ue20eGSgmrd).â For Devshop 5, Casey delved into the particulars of one of his recent blog posts, â[Things you need to know when scaling MeteorJS](http://projectricochet.com/blog/things-you-need-know-when-scaling-meteor-js#.Ue20emSgmrd).â These lessons were drawn from Project Ricochet's recent beta launch of [PushPinPlanner](http://pushpinplanner.com/) â a resource planning app that grew out of their own needs as a services-for-hire business.

"]],'

<iframe width="560" height="315" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/TdWLOQDkdG8" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>

