##Lightning Talks

- [Stefan Strohmer](http://www.linkedin.com/pub/stefan-strohmer/78/8/715) demoed [Questful](http://www.getQuestful.com), an event management app built in two weeks by his co-founder Patrick Schubert. Audience members can post and upvote questions, speakers can share supplemental material, and event hosts can post announcements and timetables.

- [Dave Kaplan](http://www.linkedin.com/in/kaptron), CTO of [Exygy](http://exygy.com/), talked through [Minimongoid](https://github.com/Exygy/minimongoid), a smart package that gives you mongoid inspired model architecture for your Meteor apps.

- [Ted Blackman](https://github.com/belisarius222) and [Matty Goodman](http://www.linkedin.com/pub/matthew-goodman/4/8aa/a94) showed off two projects that use Meteor as an interface for controlling hardware devices. [3Scan](http://www.3scan.com/) creates 3D models of tissue samples using a serial-sectioning microscope, and [Tempo Automation](http://tempoautomation.com/)'s low-cost "Pick-N-Place" robot assembles circuit boards based on uploaded design schematics.

- [Ronaldo Barbachano](https://github.com/redcap3000) demoed two Meteor apps. [Instashow](http://instashow.meteor.com) is a simple app that creates slideshows from an instagram feed or tag. [Hackerchat](http://hackerchat.meteor.com) is a social platform designed for hackathons; it was the winner of "Best Real World Application" at the [2013 Meteor Summer Hackathon](http://www.meteor.com/blog/2013/07/09/congratulations-to-the-meteor-summer-hackathon-2013-teams).

- [Geoffrey Vedernikoff](http://yef.im/) demoed [Z Mongo Admin](https://github.com/gterrono/meteor-admin-ui), a Meteor smart package that provides a Mongo admin for Meteor similar to DjangoAdmin. Z Mongo Admin won the award for "Most Technically Impressive" at the [2013 Meteor Summer Hackathon](http://www.meteor.com/blog/2013/07/09/congratulations-to-the-meteor-summer-hackathon-2013-teams).

