In addition to [tech talks](http://www.meteor.com/blog/2013/09/16/meteor-devshop-7-tech-talks-fun-with-livedata-chrome-extensions) by Avital Oliver and Jon Perl, the [August Devshop](http://www.meetup.com/Meteor-SFBay/events/129699452/) featured a strong lineup of lightning talks that showcased some of the exciting projects Meteorites have been working on:

- Troy Do explained his product AirLotz, an âAirBnB for parking lotsâ that turns garage driveways into parking spaces. He demoed the UI of the AirLotz MVP mobile app, built using Meteor.

- [James Gill](https://github.com/jagill) of [MadEye.io](http://madeye.io) demoed [jobboard.meteor.com](http://jobboard.meteor.com), an app that he built to serve as a central place for Meteor-related job openings.

- [Alex Hancock](http://twitter.com/alexjhancock) explained his [Backbone.mongo](https://github.com/alexhancock/backbone-mongo) project, which combines Meteor's minimongo with Backbone.collection, allowing you to run ad-hoc mongo queries on data in a Backbone collection. 

- [Ryan Casey](http://ryepdx.com/) talked about using Meteor to build a Bitcoin service for [CodeBounty](http://codebounty.co). He explained how they keep the Bitcoins safe and described some of the speedbumps they overcame along the way.

- [Carl Lumma](https://twitter.com/clumma) talked about using Meteor to plot data on the nation's bond options, which the Federal Reserve of St. Louis makes available. He noted the packages and APIs used in his project, including [Meteor Router](https://github.com/tmeasday/meteor-router) and [Highcharts JS](http://www.highcharts.com/).

- [Ian Serlin](https://twitter.com/spiceninja) talked about building marketplaces using the [Balanced Payments package](https://github.com/ianserlin/meteor-balanced-payments). He is currently using Balanced Payments in his production Meteor app [flavorplease.com](http://flavorplease.com), a site for easy booking of gourmet food trucks.

- Finally, [Tuhin Chakraborty](https://github.com/tuhinc) talked about his project to build a [RethinkDB module for Meteor](https://github.com/tuhinc/rethink-livedata). He described what he sees as RethinkDB's advantages over MongoDB and summarized his progress so far, which has been made possible by Meteor's modular nature. 
