Devshop 8 tech talks featured two impressive real-world apps built on Meteor. [Dirk Stevens](https://twitter.com/madewithwonder) flew in from Belgium to talk about building [Interview](http://wonderinterview.com/), an app that makes data analysis as simple as search. Meanwhile, [Tom Coleman](http://tom.thesnail.org) &mdash; of [Meteorite](https://atmosphere.meteor.com/) and [Discover Meteor](http://discovermeteor.com) fame &mdash; flew in from Australia to present [Verso](http://versoapp.com/#verso) alongside his [Percolate Studio](http://percolatestudio.com) teammates [Zoltan Olah](https://github.com/zol) and [Dominic Nguyen](https://twitter.com/domyen).

##Building Interview with Meteor

[Dirk Stevens](https://twitter.com/madewithwonder) is the CEO of [Wondergraphs](https://www.wondergraphs.com/), a small team that specializes in data analysis and visualization. In his talk, Dirk demoed his newest project [Interview](http://wonderinterview.com/), which allows you to "interview" your data with simple keyword searches like "revenue by salesperson," and then quickly see beautiful live results as charts and tables. He explained why he chose Meteor, walked us through his application structure, and talked about his approaches to styling, testing, customer development, and payments. Listening to Dirk talk, it was obvious how much more enjoyable Meteor was compared to his previous approach of integrating multiple "best of breed" web development tools. 

Dirk is hiring JavaScript developers around the globe and can be reached at dirk.stevens@wonderinterview.com.

']],'

