##Building a Production-Ready Meteor App

[Ritik Malhotra](https://twitter.com/ritikm) is the CEO of [Streem](https://www.streem.com/), a [Y Combinator](http://ycombinator.com/)-backed startup that provides a free service for storing, streaming, and sharing video. Streem is built using Meteor, and Ritik spoke on what Meteorites should think about when graduating from toy example apps to complex, large-scale production apps. He began with an overview of Streem's file structure, touched briefly on the essential packages they use, then delved into server architecture. In particular, he said developers need to solve deployment, multiple web servers, load balancing (with sticky sessions), and database scaling. Ritik covered Streem's approach to each of these, noting that there are multiple ways to scale Meteor's server side. He's hoping to soon publish resources to help other Meteorites who are working on production apps.

Ritik is recruiting for Streem's [first engineering hire](https://angel.co/streem/jobs); shoot him an e-mail at jobs@streem.com if you're interested.

