I'm happy to announce the return of [unofficial support for Meteor on Windows](http://win.meteor.com/). Building on the great work that [Tom Wijsman](https://github.com/tomwij) did to port Meteor to Windows, [Matthew Sullivan](https://github.com/shoebappa), [Gabriel Pugliese](https://github.com/gabrielhpugliese),Â and [Stephen Darnell](https://github.com/sdarnell) have contributed two [Vagrant-based](https://github.com/shoebappa/vagrant-meteor-windows) [solutions](https://docs.google.com/a/meteor.com/document/d/1zwr3qEDsosUGgulYuQQ-0umnDgQtl8BUkKNySOCHMPM/edit) and a [0.6.3.1 MSI installer](https://github.com/sdarnell/meteor/wiki/Windows). Windows users can visit [win.meteor.com](http://win.meteor.com/) to see the most up-to-date community solutions.Â 

A glance at the [roadmap](http://roadmap.meteor.com/) shows many substantial Meteor improvements in the months ahead. We're excited for all of them, and it's hard to resist the urge to put everything in the âNowâ column. An [official Windows port](https://trello.com/card/official-windows-support/508721606e02bb9d570016ae/11) is on the way. Since Meteor is still a rapidly-evolving platform, core packages need to take priority, if only for now.Â Â 

[Tom](https://twitter.com/tomwij/) stepped in to fill the need for a Windows port and published his solutions at [win.meteor.com](http://win.meteor.com/), which has been the home of unofficial, community-provided Windows support since May 2012. When Tom announced that he was stepping down from maintaining the Windows port, it was clearÂ  â on twitter, IRC, and Meteor-talk â how much the Windows port means to the Meteorites who use it. [Gabriel](https://twitter.com/gabrielsapo/), [Matthew](https://twitter.com/shoebappa/), and [Stephen](https://github.com/sdarnell) each stepped up with new solutions for Windows developers, and are now coordinating their work at [win.meteor.com](http://win.meteor.com/).Â Â 

Thank you to everyone who has contributed time and effort to Meteor on Windows, including [Mathieu Bouchard](https://github.com/matb33), [Bret Fisher](https://github.com/BretFisher), [@emgee3](https://github.com/emgee3), [Cory Simmons](https://github.com/corysimmons), and [many others](https://groups.google.com/forum/?fromgroups#!searchin/meteor-talk/windows$20meteor/meteor-talk/lSKqL5wXOnA/ogIaySpUinQJ). And thank you once more to [Tom Wijsman](https://github.com/tomwij), [Matthew Sullivan](https://github.com/shoebappa), [Gabriel Pugliese](https://github.com/gabrielhpugliese) and [Stephen Darnell](https://github.com/sdarnell).


